A GANG of heavily armed men targeted bank customers in an armed robbery in the Upper Highway on Friday.Blue Security operations manager Brian Jackson said a gang followed a bank customer from a branch to his home in Jan Smuts Highway in Winston Park at around 10.15am. A gang of five men, one of them armed with an AK47, ambushed the resident and demanded cash as he arrived outside his gate. The gang fled in a blue Chevrolet Spark with R25 000 and the victim s cellphone. No injuries were reported, he said.Hillcrest SAPS attended the scene of the crime.- Supplied24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.